<section class="section-border grid-wrapper" id="course-info">
  <h2 class="heading-large">3. Training details</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-2-3">
    <div class="text">
      <p>The successful candidate will be trained onsite and be supported by a Valkyrie tutor to achieve the Engineering qualification and functional skills. (where applicable)</p>
      <h3 class="heading-medium">Skills desired</h3>
      <p>The ideal candidate will have good command of English Language, a high standard of maths, basic IT skills and good communication skills.</p>
      <p>An interest in mechanical fields would be beneficial.</p>



      <h3 class="heading-medium">Reality check</h3>
      <p>This apprenticeship is subject to a 3 Month probationary period, which is mandatory. </p>
      <p>There will be a 1 day minimum Trial prior to offer of position. </p>

      <h3 class="heading-medium collpanel-trigger">Future prospects</h3>
      <div class="collpanel toggle-content">
        <p>Advancement to Level 3 qualification is encouraged and supported.</p>
        <p>On successful completion of Apprenticeship, there will be a Full Time position available leading to competitive salary in excess of £28k + benefits. </p>
        <p>Long term potential for career development to a more senior position. </p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="heading-medium collpanel-trigger">Personal qualities</h3>
      <div class="collpanel toggle-content">
        <p>Working on sensitive projects requires confidentiality of projects is essential.</p>
        <p>Reliability and punctuality required.</p>
        <p>Enthusiastic approach to learning </p>
        <p>You will need to work as part of a small team and at times under own initiative.</p>
        <p>You must be capable of standing during all working hours. </p>
        <p>A degree of physical work will be required. </p>
        <p>Comfortable with unclean working environments. </p>
      </div>

    </div>
    <h3 class="heading-medium collpanel-trigger">Other information</h3>
    <div class="collpanel toggle-content">
